The paper deals with the problem of multi-resolution compressed sensing (MR-CS) reconstruction, which involves the reconstruction of a low-resolution (LR) signal when there are not enough CS samples to recover a high-resolution (HR) signal. This problem is related to several areas of computer science, including information theory (cs.IT), computer vision (cs.CV), signal processing (cs.SP), multimedia (cs.MM), and social and information networks (cs.SI). However, given that the paper focuses on image reconstruction using soft-thresholding or total variation denoiser, and develops up-/down-sampling operators in transform or spatial domain, it is most likely to belong to cs.CV, followed by cs.SP, cs.MM, cs.IT, and cs.SI.
